4.04 Information Handling Obligations. Each Party will endeavor to mark Confidential Information as follows:
(a) Confidential Information first disclosed in tangible form or electronically will be marked by the Disclosing Party as "confidential" or "proprietary" or with words of similar import when provided;
(b) Confidential Information first disclosed orally or by visual display will be identified by the Disclosing Party as "confidential" or "proprietary" or with words of similar import at first disclosure and subsequently confirmed as confidential in a summary provided in an e-mail or other written communication delivered to the other Party within thirty (30) days after first disclosure;
(c) If a Sample is sent to the other Party, the Sample will be marked by the Disclosing Party as "confidential" or "proprietary" or with words of similar import at the time of disclosure.
